com.zhuinden.servicetree

Class ServiceTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.zhuinden.servicetree.ServiceTree

  • public class ServiceTree
extends java.lang.Object
    A tree that is able to hold bound services in each of its ServiceTree.Node. Also makes it possible to traverse through the tree, or any of its subtrees in a particular type of order using ServiceTree.Walk.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  ServiceTree.Node
      A node that holds its key, its children and its bound services.
      static interface  ServiceTree.Scoped
      An interface that allows you to listen for when the node your service belongs to is bound or unbound.
      static interface  ServiceTree.Walk
      The operation that is executed for each node during traverseTree(int, Walk) and traverseSubtree(Node, int, Walk).

      • traverseChain

        public void traverseChain(@NonNull
                          ServiceTree.Node node,
                          int mode,
                          @NonNull
                          ServiceTree.Walk walk)
        Traversing the chain from the node through its parents. It is equivalent to calling traverseChain(Node, int, boolean, Walk), excluding the tree root. ServiceTree.Walk.PRE_ORDER means the traversal happens from root to child. ServiceTree.Walk.POST_ORDER means the traversal happens from child to root.
        Parameters:
        node - The node that begins the chain traversal towards its parent.
        mode - The order of the traversal.
        walk - The walk executed for each element.

      • traverseChain

        public void traverseChain(@NonNull
                          ServiceTree.Node node,
                          int mode,
                          boolean includeTreeRoot,
                          @NonNull
                          ServiceTree.Walk walk)
        Traversing the chain and its parents, order depending on the specified mode. ServiceTree.Walk.PRE_ORDER means the traversal happens from root to child. ServiceTree.Walk.POST_ORDER means the traversal happens from child to root.
        Parameters:
        node - The node that begins the chain traversal towards its parent.
        mode - The order of the traversal.
        includeTreeRoot - specifies whether the tree root is included.
        walk - The walk executed for each element.
